 \log \mathrm{det}\, X^{-1} 
\log \det X^{-1} = \log (\det X)^{-1} = -\log \det X
\frac{\partial}{\partial X_{ij}} \log \det X^{-1} = -\frac{\partial}{\partial X_{ij}} \log \det X = - \frac{1}{\det X} \frac{\partial \det X}{\partial X_{ij}} = - \frac{1}{\det X} \mathrm{adj}(X)_{ji} = - (X^{-1})_{ji}
